subSubSection.paragraph:
EMENDED DIAGNOSIS: A medium-sized shrew (
tables 2
, 
14
) with a medium build and uniformly dark pelage, feet, and tail (light chocolate to black; 
fig. 36
). The tail is shorter than head-andbody length. The hind foot is somewhat short relative to head-and-body length (
fig. 17
), and usually dark brown to black. The skull is broad, and quite angular, with a prominent maxillary process, broad palate, and dentition with a large occlusal area relative to palatal area (
fig. 37B
). The interorbital region is unusually narrow, which enhances the prominence of the braincase breadth and maxillary process (
fig. 10
). Rostral length makes up a large proportion of skull length (
fig. 10
).
